            <div align="left" style="margin-top:10px; padding: 10px"><br><br>
                <p>Jaysen had been raving about this place long before we actually tried it together. Usually, when people rave about something– whether it be a restaurant or a movie– it raises your expectations to such a level that they will never be met. This was not the case for Oscar’s Mexican Seafood, a cozy taco shop just a few minutes’ walk from the sunny shores of Pacific Beach.</p>
                                
            <div align="center" style="margin:30px">
                <img src="images/reviews/oscars/storefront.jpg" width="80%" height="80%">
            </div>
            
                <p>We walked around the beach until 2:30, when the happy hour ($1 tacos) started. The décor was perhaps a little nicer than your average taco shop, and the menu was beautifully hand written. They had a variety of good looking stuff– different types of fish tacos, a breakfast burrito (for only $3.50!), ceviche, quesadillas, fish stew, etc.– everything you would expect from a Mexican fish taco shop. Being the broke college students that we are, we stuck to the happy hour and grabbed ten fish tacos.</p>
                
            <div align="center" style="margin:30px">
                <img src="images/reviews/oscars/sign.jpg" width="40%" height="40%">
            </div>
                
                <p>They definitely didn’t skimp out on the goods; a delicious nugget of freshly fried fish lay at the bottom of a warm corn tortilla, loaded with fresh lettuce, onion, and cilantro (and of course a side of limes). Oh, and when I say delicious nugget, I really mean it. The fried fish had a perfect shell of crispy goodness, with a tender heart of moist and steaming white fish. The tacos would taste great by themselves, but Oscar’s really goes above and beyond with their hot sauce selection, and I made it a point to try all half dozen of them.</p> 
     
            <div align="center" style="margin:30px">
                <img src="images/reviews/oscars/sauce.jpg" width="80%" height="80%">
            </div>
                
                <p>But what really pushes Oscar’s ahead of the competition isn’t just the great happy hour deal, or the perfectly prepared fish tacos, or even outstanding selection of hot sauces. What makes Oscar’s the best Mexican taco shop in town are its three homemade sauces that we drenched all over our tacos. Each sauce is completely unique from the other, and each one is delicious in its own right. I recommend starting with the creamy green sauce, which was our favorite. We have no idea what’s in it but we promise you’ll love it.</p>
                <p>And there you have it, folks. Due to the outstanding value and quality of Oscar’s happy hour, we rank it as one our Best Happy Hour Specials in the greater La Jolla area. Next time you have a weekday off, take a trip to Pacific Beach, walk along the pier and up the shores, and once you are good and hungry, go fill yourself up with the best $1 fish taco you’ve ever had.</p>
